# Backend Communication Design Patterns
    This repository showcases various backend communication design patterns implemented in Node.js. These patterns are key for creating scalable and efficient server-side applications.

Patterns Included
    Short Polling
    Long Polling
    Server-Sent Events (SSE)
    Push Communication
    Connection Pooling
    Streaming

Usage
    Each pattern is demonstrated in its respective folder with sample code and instructions. Navigate to a specific folder to view or test the implementation.